@startuml mesmerize-sqs-request-reply-correlation
title Mesmerize — SQS Request/Reply + Correlation Identifier\nPer target-service reply queue · Per-operation timeout · ADR-014

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false

participant "Caller Service\n(e.g. session-service)" as Caller
queue "billing.requests" as Req
participant "billing-evidence-service" as Billing
queue "billing.replies" as Rep

== 1. Build request ==
Caller -> Caller : correlationId = UUID()\nreplyTo = "billing.replies"\ntimeout = op-specific (e.g. 5s / 30s / 120s)\nenvelope: tenantId, messageType, payload\n(**no** patient id / EHR token)

== 2. Send request ==
Caller -> Req : SendMessage(request)\nMessageAttributes: correlationId, replyTo, tenantId

== 3. Process ==
Billing -> Req : ReceiveMessage
Billing -> Billing : Validate tenantId\nExecute work (e.g. compute suggestions)
Billing -> Rep : SendMessage(reply)\n**same correlationId**\npayload = result **or** error (enriched)

== 4. Correlate reply ==
Caller -> Rep : Long-poll / receive\n**filter MessageAttributes.correlationId**
Caller -> Caller : Match correlationId\nComplete wait **or** timeout → fail path

note over Caller, Rep
  **Correlation Identifier**
  Only the reply with matching correlationId
  completes this wait. Other replies ignored
  by this waiter (or routed to other waiters).
end note

note right of Caller
  Interactive SMART/device hot path
  prefers **REST** to owning service (ADR-014 matrix).
  Use SQS RR when work is offloaded / durable.
end note

@enduml
